						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab (A. 34, left side) in the Museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōvidēva—A.D. 1170.</p>						

						<p>This short inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">4th year of the</hi> reign of <hi rend="bold">Rāyamurāri Sōyidēva, Vikṛita, Āshāḍha, Amāvāsyā, Wednesday</hi> corresponding regularly to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1170 July 15, Wednesday.</hi> It states that <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Chauḍarasa,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Manneya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Tardavāḍi.</hi> made a gift of land to the school at <hi rend="bold">Pauṭhage</hi> (modern Sāloṭgi).</p>						

						</summary>
